 class="photo-gallery-slider-number">9</span><span class="photo-gallery-slider-of">of</span><span class="photo-gallery-slider-number">9</span></div><div class="photo-gallery-slider-captions-credit"><div class="photo-credit-text js-image-credit"><a href="#">Image Credit</a><template><div class="tippy-credit"><p>The Wilson Center</p></div></template></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></figure><div class="single-promo -has-image"><div class="single-promo-inner"><div class="single-promo-image"><picture><source srcset="/sites/default/files/styles/2up_image/public/media/uploads/images/FPFP%20Alumni%20Canada%20Iceland.webp" type="image/webp"/><img src="/sites/default/files/styles/2up_image/public/media/uploads/images/FPFP%20Alumni%20Canada%20Iceland.png" width="620" height="440" alt="Image - FPFP Alumni Trip Canada Iceland" loading="lazy"></picture></div><div class="single-promo-content"><h3 class="single-promo-title h3">Want to Learn More about our Alumni Study Trips?</h3><p class="single-promo-text -serif">The Wilson Center&#039;s Office of Congressional Relations has hosted several trips to locations around the world in order for Congressional staff to learn about the US relationship with various countries and critical foreign policy matters.</p><a href="/foreign-policy-fellowship-program-staff-delegation-trips" class="single-promo-button btn -outlined">Click Here to Learn More</a></div></div></div><div class="leadership-grid"><div class="leadership-grid-inner"><div class="leadership-grid-content"><div class="leadership-grid-intro"><h2 class="leadership-grid-intro-title h5">For More Information Contact</h2><div class="leadership-grid-intro-text wysiwyg-content"><p>Foreign Policy Fellowship Program Project Director: Paige Rotunda</p><p>Email: <strong>paige.rotunda@wilsoncenter.org</strong></p></div></div><div class="leadership-grid-group"><h3 class="leadership-grid-group-title h5">Congressional Relations Staff</h3><div class="leadership-grid-group-people"><a class